span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">over the lack of a national-wide strategy for a high speed rail network to provide a context for decisions which will be being taken in the next few years.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> We will be responding in more detail to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">DfT’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> consultation on “</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">HS2 Phase Two: proposed line of route from the West Midlands to Manchester and Leeds</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">” in due course.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We produced a position paper on HS2 in October 2009 and revised this in May 2011 when we responded to the HOCTC inquiry into the strategic case for High Speed rail. Both these documents are in your files. The basis of our views then is largely unchanged though circumstances have moved on.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">In summary we see the main argument for HS2 as primarily being an increase in capacity to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">meet growth beyond the capacity of the existing system and we also believe it will bring economic benefits to the north. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">However, it is vitally important that concentration on the HS2 project does not deprive the existing route network of investment or continuing development</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> holistic </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">view of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">HS2 as part of a new railway system</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> needs to be taken. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">It is also vitally important that - </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">he ability and the intention for HS trains to run on to the current route network to serve destinations </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">such as Liverpool, Preston </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">and  Cumbria</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> is emphasised. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Good interchange is provided between High Speed Trains and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">modern</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> local trains to enable passengers to start and finish their rail journeys as conveniently and comfortably as possible. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Service levels on the existing West Coast Main Line are kept at a good frequency (certainly no worse than now) between </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">centres</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> of population not served by HSR in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">order</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> to maintain connectivity. N</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">owhere</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> should have an inferior service to the current frequency after opening of HS2</span><span style="color:#000080; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">.</span><span style="color:#000080; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Full use should be made of the capacity freed up</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> by HS services.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Every effort should be made to speed up the whole process of building HS2, more quickly than the existing timescales – we have capacity issues </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">now</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal"> at certain times of the year/ day on many routes and this will become increasingly exacerbated.  </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">Fares are priced reasonably – this must not be a service exclusively for the better off passenger.  </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>